---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-05-19';
---

<Layout title="Now — Aojie Yuan" description="What I'm focused on right now.">
  <main>
    <Header current="now" />

    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
      <h1>What I'm focused on, right now.</h1>
      <p class="updated">Updated {new Date(lastUpdated).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })} · Los Angeles</p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>Doing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>AEGIS.</strong> Open-source pre-execution firewall and audit
          layer for AI agents. Just shipped per-tenant Policy DSL with
          fail-safe semantics and a Monaco-based editor in the Cockpit.
          Looking for design-partner deployments — reach out if you're
          running production agents and want to talk.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Design partners.</strong> Talking to a handful of teams
          running AI agents in production. The goal is a small first
          cohort using AEGIS in real workloads, with a tight feedback
          loop into the next set of features (alignment auditing, custom
          rule learning, MCP traffic inspection).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>M.S. at USC.</strong> First-year. F-1 status, which
          shapes what I can take on outside school — open to
          collaborations and design-partner relationships, not full-time
          roles.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Thinking about</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>How to surface tenant-specific false positives back into the
          policy layer without making customers feel like they're
          labelling data for free.</li>
        <li>Whether agent-alignment auditing (LlamaFirewall-style CoT
          inspection) should be a separate service or another DSL signal.</li>
        <li>The cleanest way to ship a Tauri-packaged desktop installer
          that ships gateway + cockpit + SDK demos as one .dmg / .exe.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Not doing right now</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Full-time roles, freelance contract work, and anything else my
          visa would frown on.</li>
        <li>SSO / WorkOS integration. Will revisit when the first
          enterprise customer asks.</li>
        <li>Postgres support in AEGIS. SQLite is fine for self-host;
          Postgres lands when a paying customer needs it.</li>
        <li>Anything cryptocurrency-adjacent.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Reach out</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:aojieyua@usc.edu">aojieyua@usc.edu</a> · I read every
        message and reply to most within a day or two.
      </p>

      <p class="meta">
        This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener">/now page</a>
        — a Derek Sivers convention.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    main {
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem 6rem;
    }
    .page-head {
      margin: 4rem 0 3rem;
    }
    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.13em;
      margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.9rem);
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin: 0 0 0.8rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.012em;
    }
    .updated {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .prose {
      font-size: 1.04rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .prose h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      margin: 2.6rem 0 0.8rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }
    .prose ul {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
      margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    }
    .prose li {
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    }
    .prose em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    .prose strong {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .meta {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
